parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Slipped Cylinder Sleeve
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine due to a slipped cylinder sleeve can cause the engine to seize, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

the engine dies and won't restart
the vehicle shutters when coming to a stop with the air conditioner on.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag Warning Lamp Illumination due to Faulty Seat Belt Buckle and Grounding System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty design of the seat belt buckle and grounding system can cause the airbag warning lamp to stay on, potentially masking real airbag system problems, which can lead to a safety risk if not addressed.
symptoms: The airbag warning lamp remains illuminated
indicating a potential problem with the airbag system
but the issue may be due to a faulty seat belt buckle and grounding system rather than an actual airbag system malfunction.
